64.7	Magnum_opus	Magnum opus	Magnum opus (plural: magna opera, also opus magnum / opera magna), from the Latin meaning "great work", refers to the largest, and perhaps the best, greatest, most popular, or most renowned achievement of a writer, artist, or composer.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/HBalzac.jpg/220px-HBalzac.jpg
